This paper deals with the semantics of fuzzy if-then rules, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves formalization, axiomatization, and data analysis, which are typical topics in machine learning and data mining, suggesting cs.LG, cs.DB, and cs.DM as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with fuzzy logic, which is a subfield of mathematical logic, indicating cs.FL as a possible sub-category.
